<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="33" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,852,2032]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,962,987]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can easily be distinguished from its congeners by the following combination of characters: a great body depth (
<number box="[454,527,999,1023]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="28.5" valueMax="29.0" valueMin="28.0">28–29</number>
% SL; other species usually 
<number box="[844,873,999,1023]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="27.0">27</number>
% SL) longer head length (
<number box="[1175,1247,999,1023]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="30.5" valueMax="31.0" valueMin="30.0">30–31</number>
% SL; other species usually 
<number box="[288,319,1034,1058]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="28.0">28</number>
%), head profile oblique, about 
<number box="[669,711,1034,1058]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="130.0">130</number>
degree angle (other species usually 
<number box="[1115,1198,1034,1058]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="112.5" valueMax="130.0" valueMin="95.0">95–130</number>
degrees); head depth (
<number box="[159,231,1071,1095]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="26.5" valueMax="27.0" valueMin="26.0">26–27</number>
% SL; other species usually 
<number box="[564,593,1071,1095]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="26.0">26</number>
% SL); eyes high on head (interorbital width 
<number box="[1124,1195,1071,1095]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="32.5" valueMax="34.0" valueMin="31.0">31–34</number>
% HL); small orbital diameter 
<number box="[256,327,1106,1130]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="24.5" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="24.0">24–25</number>
% HL, only 
<taxonomicName box="[463,642,1107,1131]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Malacanthidae" genus="Branchiostegus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sawakinensis">
<emphasis box="[463,642,1107,1131]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">B. sawakinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[696,787,1107,1131]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Malacanthidae" genus="Branchiostegus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albus">
<emphasis box="[696,787,1107,1131]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">B. albus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with small orbital diameters, 
<number box="[1122,1193,1106,1130]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="23.5" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="23.0">23–24</number>
% HL) long predorsal length (
<number box="[236,265,1143,1167]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="35.0">35</number>
% SL; other species usually 
<number box="[584,655,1143,1167]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="31.0" valueMax="32.0" valueMin="30.0">30–32</number>
% SL, rarely 
<number box="[803,875,1143,1167]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="33.5" valueMax="34.0" valueMin="33.0">33–34</number>
% SL), deep body (
<number box="[1091,1158,1143,1167]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="28.5" valueMax="29.0" valueMin="28.0">28-29</number>
% SL; other species usually 
<number box="[199,273,1178,1202]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="25.5" valueMax="27.0" valueMin="24.0">24–27</number>
%, rarely, only in 
<taxonomicName box="[468,607,1180,1203]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Malacanthidae" genus="Branchiostegus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[468,607,1180,1203]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">B. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[660,842,1179,1203]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Malacanthidae" genus="Branchiostegus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="semifasciatus">
<emphasis box="[660,842,1179,1203]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">B. semifasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<number box="[855,927,1178,1202]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="28.5" valueMax="29.0" valueMin="28.0">28–29</number>
% SL); wide body (
<number box="[1143,1214,1178,1202]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="14.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="14.0">14–15</number>
% SL; other species usually 
<number box="[240,309,1215,1239]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="12.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="11.0">11–13</number>
% SL); number of first arch gill rakers low 
<number box="[807,835,1215,1239]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="18.0">18</number>
+ 
<number box="[868,882,1215,1239]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="1.0">1</number>
rudimentary, most other species 
<number box="[1259,1331,1215,1239]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="21.0" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="18.0">18–24</number>
, modally 
<number box="[151,224,1250,1274]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="20.5" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="19.0">19–22</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,852,2032]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">
Fresh colouration includes: Upper body rosy red with flecks of pearly-silver scales and pearly pinkish-silver lower body and anterior lower throat regions; dorsal to pectoral to about the lateral line with a large golden yellow area with a silver central patch; lower head region bluish-white from about a horizontal line from lower cheek above the preopercular angle to the pectoral fin base; lateral head metallic golden from anterior orbit to about midorbit dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[318,384,1431,1455]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,754,777]" captionTargetBox="[234,1358,285,728]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[228,1365,268,729]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Fresh colouration of 329 mm SL (holotype, MUFS 36081) specimen of B. saitoi caught by hook and line, 14 May 2011, Batangas, Laiya, Philippines; photo by J. Saito." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280553/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 
<number box="[371,384,1431,1455]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName box="[410,504,1432,1455]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Malacanthidae" genus="Branchiostegus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saitoi">
<emphasis box="[410,504,1432,1455]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">B. saitoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has distinct head, tail and body fresh colouration: a prominent dark predorsal ridge overlying yellow-orange pigment reaching to a vertical above the anterior orbital rim (
<figureCitation box="[1219,1330,1466,1490]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2" captionStart-2="FIGURE 3" captionStartId-0="2.[151,250,754,777]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,250,1563,1586]" captionStartId-2="4.[151,250,1142,1165]" captionTargetBox-0="[234,1358,285,728]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1436,846,1542]" captionTargetBox-2="[168,1424,191,1120]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[228,1365,268,729]" captionTargetId-1="figure@3.[151,1436,846,1542]" captionTargetId-2="figure@4.[139,1424,161,1121]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionTargetPageId-2="4" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. Fresh colouration of 329 mm SL (holotype, MUFS 36081) specimen of B. saitoi caught by hook and line, 14 May 2011, Batangas, Laiya, Philippines; photo by J. Saito." captionText-1="FIGURE 2. Freshly preserved holotype 329 mm SL; photo by the second author." captionText-2="FIGURE 3. Head of the holotype of B. saitoi (329 mm SL); photo by J. Saito." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/280553/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/280554/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/280555/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">
Figs. 
<number box="[1286,1330,1466,1490]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
</figureCitation>
); (a dark more prominent predorsal ridge found only in 
<taxonomicName box="[684,861,1503,1527]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Malacanthidae" genus="Branchiostegus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="semifasciatus">
<emphasis box="[684,861,1503,1527]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">B semifasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from West Africa, but it lacks underlying yelloworange colour); upper lip orange-yellow (over maxillary) and white (over premaxillary and mandible) iris goldengreen; snout reddish; lateral head from above about mid orbit to top of head red; skin over dorsal tips of branchiostegals characteristically bright yellow (
<figureCitation box="[656,726,1610,1634]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1142,1165]" captionTargetBox="[168,1424,191,1120]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[139,1424,161,1121]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Head of the holotype of B. saitoi (329 mm SL); photo by J. Saito." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280555/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 
<number box="[711,726,1610,1634]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
); dorsal fin membrane translucent pink, yellow distally along entire margin of the fin; and anal fin membranes translucent to pinkish white; pelvics white with overlying yellow; dorsal upper pectoral rays dusky, ventral half yellow; caudal characteristically coloured among all congeners (although somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[501,597,1719,1743]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Malacanthidae" genus="Branchiostegus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wardi">
<emphasis box="[501,597,1719,1743]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">B. wardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); a central translucent horizontal band, most of the area dorsal to the band bright yellow, upper margin black with outer margin white; below the clear central caudal band also bright yellow for about one third of the ventral caudal area, followed by a little more than third of the caudal black then a little less than a third of the ventral caudal white (
<figureCitation box="[648,725,1826,1850]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,754,777]" captionTargetBox="[234,1358,285,728]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[228,1365,268,729]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Fresh colouration of 329 mm SL (holotype, MUFS 36081) specimen of B. saitoi caught by hook and line, 14 May 2011, Batangas, Laiya, Philippines; photo by J. Saito." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280553/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[739,753,1826,1850]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1563,1586]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,846,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,846,1542]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Freshly preserved holotype 329 mm SL; photo by the second author." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280554/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">2</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[807,823,1826,1850]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1755,1778]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,151,1733]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,127,1733]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Freshly preserved colouration of the tail of B. saitoi, 329 mm SL (holotype) photo by the second author." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280557/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">
<number box="[807,823,1826,1850]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
