<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="34" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1630,1873]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1633,1658]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Distribution</emphasis>
. Known only from Bayangas, Laiya, 
<collectingCountry box="[793,919,1633,1657]" name="Philippines" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Philippines</collectingCountry>
(
<number box="[940,968,1633,1657]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="13.0">13</number>
<geoCoordinate box="[968,1080,1630,1657]" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" precision="92" value="0.64166665">
0 
<number box="[987,1041,1633,1657]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="38.5">38.5</number>
’ N
</geoCoordinate>
, 
<number box="[1095,1137,1633,1657]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="121.0">121</number>
<geoCoordinate box="[1137,1238,1630,1657]" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" precision="92" value="0.42666668">
0 
<number box="[1151,1205,1633,1657]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="25.6">25.6</number>
’ E
</geoCoordinate>
) at 
<number box="[1302,1400,1633,1657]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="215.0" valueMax="220.0" valueMin="210.0">210–220</number>
M depths, it is possibly endemic; but as it is very rare, and probably inhabits burrows as do other tilefishes, 
<taxonomicName box="[1342,1436,1670,1693]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Malacanthidae" genus="Branchiostegus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saitoi">
<emphasis box="[1342,1436,1670,1693]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">B. saitoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may ultimately be found at other localities.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="34" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1630,1873]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1741,1765]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Etymology.</emphasis>
A new species of 
<taxonomicName box="[539,713,1741,1765]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Malacanthidae" genus="Branchiostegus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[539,713,1741,1765]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Branchiostegus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first caught off Batangas Laiya, 
<collectingCountry box="[1131,1257,1741,1765]" name="Philippines" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Philippines</collectingCountry>
in 
<number box="[1293,1352,1741,1765]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="2009.0">2009</number>
, photographed and eaten. Two years passed before two more specimens were caught by J. Saito, an amateur angler from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,215,1814,1837]" name="Japan" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Japan</collectingCountry>
in April, 
<number box="[342,400,1813,1837]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="2011.0">2011</number>
. Without J. Saito’s considerable efforts and interest, this species would have remained unknown. The new species is herein named in his honor.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
